    {
      "para_id": "Q000989.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(1) In Karzida , where since the beginning of time there never had been a ĝipar built and no en priestess had dwelt , Amar-Suena , whose name was proclaimed by Enlil in Nibru , the steadfast supporter of Enlil's temple , the just god , the Utu of his land , the powerful king , king of Urim , king of the four quarters , the beloved of Nanna , built his holy ĝipar for Nanna of Karzida , his beloved master , ( and ) made his beloved en priestess enter it . In so doing Amar-Suena will lengthen the days ( of his life ) . He dedicated it for his well-being to him ."
    }
  ],
